      "body" : "I installed the most minimal image (the cloud image) of the 2016-03-18 daily.\r\nThis comes with Python3, not Python2. There has also been [a lot of public attention](https://encrypted.google.com/search?q=python+3+ubuntu+16.04) about this.\r\n\r\nIt's very possible that you got 2.x as a dependency of something.\r\n`python --version` will never return a 3.x version. Python 3 is always called `python3`, so you should do `python3 --version`.\r\n",
